      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACCKA COOPER NZ (4) turned in a good effort at his latest run to get home by a narrow margin over 1660m at Albion Park on June 11. Tackles a similar assignment and he can get the job done again. BARLOR HEAVEN (9) was unplaced two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he copped a check and broke, finishing 11 metres away in fifth over 1780m at this track. May just need a bit of luck at some point from this difficult draw. Meets a similar line up so he is sure to be a force with any luck. BOLZANO NZ (6) was out of the money two runs ago then overcame a break to get the prize by 1.1 metres over 1780m at this circuit a week ago. Only needs to get things right to be in the money again. TURBO TOMMY (1) is worth some thought based on his third over 2200m at Marburg two runs ago. Include from the coveted pegs draw.",
